<paragraph id="8BA03698FFB8342375C76D1B149AF9AB" blockId="2.[151,510,1591,1618]" box="[151,510,1591,1618]" pageId="2" pageNumber="570">
<heading id="D0E881F4FFB8342375C76D1B149AF9AB" bold="true" box="[151,510,1591,1618]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="2" pageNumber="570" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B96BEA8AFFB8342375C76D1B149AF9AB" bold="true" box="[151,510,1591,1618]" pageId="2" pageNumber="570">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C1F4D1BFFB8342375BE6D1B149AF9AB" authority="Hebard, 1928" authorityName="Hebard" authorityYear="1928" box="[238,510,1591,1618]" class="Insecta" family="Phalangopsidae" genus="Aclodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96BEA8AFFB8342375BE6D1B1429F9A8" bold="true" box="[238,333,1591,1618]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="570">Aclodes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8E4B69FFB8342374046D1B149AF9AB" author="Hebard, M." box="[340,510,1591,1617]" pageId="2" pageNumber="570" pagination="79 - 124" refId="ref7325" refString="Hebard, M. (1928) Studies in the Dermaptera and Orthoptera of Colombia. Fifth paper. Orthopterous family Gryllidae. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 54 (2), 79 - 124." type="journal article" year="1928">Hebard, 1928</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3056513FFB8342275C76D53118EFE57" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="571" pageId="2" pageNumber="570" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA03698FFB8342375C76D531136F8B7" blockId="2.[151,1437,1663,2014]" pageId="2" pageNumber="570">
<emphasis id="B96BEA8AFFB8342375C76D53147BF963" bold="true" box="[151,287,1663,1689]" pageId="2" pageNumber="570">Comments.</emphasis>
This genus is very speciose, and currently includes 35 species, with a wide distribution from 
<collectingCountry id="F3087608FFB8342370736D5310F8F963" box="[1315,1436,1663,1689]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="2" pageNumber="570">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="F3087608FFB8342375E36D881582F944" box="[179,230,1700,1726]" name="Peru" pageId="2" pageNumber="570">Peru</collectingCountry>
and northern South America, with a presence on a couple of islands near 
<collectingCountry id="F3087608FFB8342371456D8F11ECF947" box="[1045,1160,1699,1725]" name="Venezuela" pageId="2" pageNumber="570">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8E4B69FFB8342371C66D8F101DF947" author="Cigliano, M. M. &amp; Braun, H. &amp; Eades, D. C. &amp; Otte, D." box="[1174,1401,1699,1726]" pageId="2" pageNumber="570" refId="ref6650" refString="Cigliano, M. M., Braun, H., Eades, D. C. &amp; Otte, D. (2022) Orthoptera Species File. Version 5.0 / 5.0. Available from: http: // Orthoptera. SpeciesFile. org (accessed 30 April 2022)" type="url" year="2022">
Cigliano 
<emphasis id="B96BEA8AFFB8342371AF6D88104BF947" box="[1279,1327,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="570">et al</emphasis>
. 2022
</bibRefCitation>
). It differs from the morphologically similar genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C1F4D1BFFB8342377FD6DEB1649F91B" authorityName="Desutter-Grandcolas" authorityYear="1992" box="[685,813,1735,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Phalangopsidae" genus="Paraclodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96BEA8AFFB8342377FD6DEB1649F91B" box="[685,813,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="570">Paraclodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in that the males have the tegmina projecting from the middle of the abdomen onwards and with strong parallel longitudinal veins. The females are distinguished by their tegmina, often reaching the first abdominal tergite posterior margin (Desutter-Grandcolas 1992), except 
<taxonomicName id="4C1F4D1BFFB8342370146C23148CF8B7" authority="(Nischk &amp; Otte 2000)" baseAuthorityName="Nischk &amp; Otte" baseAuthorityYear="2000" class="Insecta" family="Phalangopsidae" genus="Aclodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cryptos">
<emphasis id="B96BEA8AFFB8342370146C23158DF8B7" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="570">Aclodes cryptos</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8E4B69FFB8342375A86C1F1484F8B7" author="Nischk, F. &amp; Otte, D." box="[248,480,1843,1869]" pageId="2" pageNumber="570" pagination="229 - 254" refId="ref7565" refString="Nischk, F. &amp; Otte, D. (2000) Bioacoustics, ecology and systematics of Ecuadorian rainforest crickets (Orthoptera: Gryllidae: Phalangopsinae), with a description of four new genera and ten new species. Journal of Orthoptera Research, 9, 229 - 254. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3503651" type="journal article" year="2000">Nischk &amp; Otte 2000</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, with the tegmina reaching the middle of the abdomen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA03698FFB8342375976C7B11CEF843" blockId="2.[151,1437,1663,2014]" pageId="2" pageNumber="570">
<emphasis id="B96BEA8AFFB8342375976C7B1437F88B" box="[199,339,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="570">
<taxonomicName id="4C1F4D1BFFB8342375976C7B142AF88B" authorityName="Chopard" authorityYear="1923" box="[199,334,1879,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Phalangopsidae" genus="Uvaroviella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Uvaroviella</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
is a Caribbean genus with 17 species that need to be re-studied. Possibly, the three continental species still included in 
<emphasis id="B96BEA8AFFB8342374F66C571755F86F" box="[422,561,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="570">
<taxonomicName id="4C1F4D1BFFB8342374F66C571749F86F" authorityName="Chopard" authorityYear="1923" box="[422,557,1915,1941]" class="Insecta" family="Phalangopsidae" genus="Uvaroviella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Uvaroviella</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
which are only known from their females, should be included in the future in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1F4D1BFFB8342375C76CB31594F843" authorityName="Hebard" authorityYear="1928" box="[151,240,1951,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Phalangopsidae" genus="Aclodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96BEA8AFFB8342375C76CB31594F843" box="[151,240,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="570">Aclodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, after finding the respective males that allow their generic affiliation to be identified.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA03698FFB8342275C76CE81594FEE7" blockId="2.[151,1437,1663,2014]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,151,429]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="571" pageId="2" pageNumber="570">
For 
<collectingCountry id="F3087608FFB8342375946CEF1451F827" box="[196,309,1987,2013]" name="Colombia" pageId="2" pageNumber="570">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8E4B69FFB83423746F6CEF1486F827" author="Hebard, M." box="[319,482,1987,2013]" pageId="2" pageNumber="570" pagination="79 - 124" refId="ref7325" refString="Hebard, M. (1928) Studies in the Dermaptera and Orthoptera of Colombia. Fifth paper. Orthopterous family Gryllidae. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 54 (2), 79 - 124." type="journal article" year="1928">Hebard (1928)</bibRefCitation>
mentions the presence of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1F4D1BFFB8342376526CEF11E9F827" authority="(Caudell 1918)" baseAuthorityName="Caudell" baseAuthorityYear="1918" box="[770,1165,1987,2013]" class="Insecta" family="Phalangopsidae" genus="Aclodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculatum">
<emphasis id="B96BEA8AFFB8342376526CEF16B9F827" box="[770,989,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="570">Aclodes maculatum</emphasis>
(Caudell 1918)
</taxonomicName>
, described initially from 
<collectingCountry id="F3087608FFB9342275C76BBB15AEFF4B" box="[151,202,151,177]" name="Peru" pageId="3" pageNumber="571">Peru</collectingCountry>
but with notable morphological differences. Hebard, at that time, did not study the internal genitalia; it was not a common practice of the time for the descriptions of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1F4D1BFFB9342277B96B971602FF2F" authorityName="Oliver" authorityYear="1789" box="[745,870,187,213]" class="Magnoliopsida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="571" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="order">Orthoptera</taxonomicName>
. Perhaps with the study of the male genitalia it will be possible to resolve this problem, with the tegmina moderately developed, as occurs in many recently described species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA03698FFB9342275976A0B118EFE57" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,429]" pageId="3" pageNumber="571">
Recently, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8E4B69FFB9342274686A0B17F9FEB8" author="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J. &amp; Gutierrez, Y. &amp; Bacca, T." box="[312,669,295,322]" pageId="3" pageNumber="571" pagination="201 - 224" refId="ref6032" refString="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J., Gutierrez, Y. &amp; Bacca, T. (2016) New and little known Orthoptera (Ensifera and Caelifera) from the Nambi River Natural Reserve, Narino, Colombia. Zootaxa, 4162 (2), 201 - 224. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4162.2.1" type="journal article" year="2016">
Cadena-Castañeda 
<emphasis id="B96BEA8AFFB9342277416A0B1727FEBB" box="[529,579,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="571">et al</emphasis>
. (2016)
</bibRefCitation>
recorded the presence of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1F4D1BFFB9342276946A0B103FFEBB" authority="(Gorochov, 2007)" baseAuthorityName="Gorochov" baseAuthorityYear="2007" box="[964,1371,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Phalangopsidae" genus="Aclodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="571" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nebulosa">
<emphasis id="B96BEA8AFFB9342276946A0B11EEFEBB" box="[964,1162,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="571">Aclodes nebulosa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8E4B69FFB9342271CA6A0B1037FEBB" author="Gorochov, A. V." box="[1178,1363,295,321]" pageId="3" pageNumber="571" pagination="1183 - 1195" refId="ref7116" refString="Gorochov, A. V. (2007) New and little known crickets of the subfamily Phalangopsinae (Orthoptera, Gryllidae). 4. Neotropical genus Uvaroviella. Zoologicheskii Zhurnal, 86 (10), 1183 - 1195. https: // doi. org / 10.1134 / S 0013873806040087" type="journal article" year="2007">Gorochov, 2007</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(then known as 
<taxonomicName id="4C1F4D1BFFB9342274586A671648FE9F" authority="Gorochov, 2007" authorityName="Gorochov" authorityYear="2007" box="[264,812,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Phalangopsidae" genus="Uvaroviella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="571" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nebulosa" subGenus="Holacla">
<emphasis id="B96BEA8AFFB9342274586A6714E9FE9F" box="[264,397,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="571">Uvaroviella</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B96BEA8AFFB9342274CD6A671493FE9F" box="[413,503,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="571">Holacla</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B96BEA8AFFB9342277586A671709FE9F" box="[520,621,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="571">nebulosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8E4B69FFB9342277246A671648FE9F" author="Gorochov, A. V." box="[628,812,331,357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="571" pagination="1183 - 1195" refId="ref7116" refString="Gorochov, A. V. (2007) New and little known crickets of the subfamily Phalangopsinae (Orthoptera, Gryllidae). 4. Neotropical genus Uvaroviella. Zoologicheskii Zhurnal, 86 (10), 1183 - 1195. https: // doi. org / 10.1134 / S 0013873806040087" type="journal article" year="2007">Gorochov, 2007</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
), in the Rio Ñambi Nature Reserve, south of the department of 
<collectingRegion id="49DBF87AFFB9342275A36A431420FE73" box="[243,324,367,393]" country="Colombia" name="Narino" pageId="3" pageNumber="571">Nariño</collectingRegion>
. This is the only species with a reliable and confirmed record for 
<collectingCountry id="F3087608FFB9342271476A4311EDFE73" box="[1047,1161,367,393]" name="Colombia" pageId="3" pageNumber="571">Colombia</collectingCountry>
. Now the second species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1F4D1BFFB9342275E66ABF146BFE57" authorityName="Hebard" authorityYear="1928" box="[182,271,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Phalangopsidae" genus="Aclodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="571" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96BEA8AFFB9342275E66ABF146BFE57" box="[182,271,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="571">Aclodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the country is described, coming from the caves of the Andes in northern 
<collectingCountry id="F3087608FFB9342271236ABF1181FE57" box="[1139,1253,403,429]" name="Colombia" pageId="3" pageNumber="571">Colombia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
